<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880908-0158 </DOCNO><HL> International Corporate Report: B.A.T Industries PLC </HL><SO> </SO><CO> BTI </CO><IN> ERN </IN><TEXT>   B.A.T Industries PLC, the British group that last month won an eight-month takeover battle for Farmers Group Inc. of the U.S., said pretax profit rose 6.3% in the second quarter and 11% in the first half.    The company said its tobacco, paper and financial-services divisions contributed strong results but retailing profit declined.    Profit before taxes in the second quarter increased to #419 million ($713.6 million) from #394 million a year earlier. Sales rose 4.3%, to #4.36 billion ($7.43 billion) from #4.18 billion.    For the half, pretax profit rose to #711 million from #642 million a year earlier, while sales increased 6%, to #8.47 billion from #7.99 billion.    Profit after taxes and minority interests rose 5.4% in the second quarter, to #254 million pounds from #241 million, and grew 8.5% in the half, to #422 million from #389 million. </TEXT></DOC>